##29-year-old dead Doctor Peng Yinhua's last 20 days

Wechat, boyangcongpeople

The function introduces, peels off the human shell, records the real sensible life. Presented by the in-depth Reporting Department of the Beijing News.

Had it not been for the epidemic, Peng Yinhua's life would have only just begun. He was 29 years old, approaching his 30th birthday, and only last year officially became a respiratory physician at the First People's Hospital in Jiangxia district, he had planned a two-year-late wedding for her on Feb. 1; his wife is six months pregnant and, unsurprisingly, he will be a father in June.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A memorial service for Peng Yinhua

By Wei Furong and Liang Jingyi, Beijing News

Editor | Xiaoshu Chen proofread | Jingning Xue

This article is about 3891 words long and takes about 8 minutes to read

Peng Yinhua, 29, is gone.

He is the First People's Hospital in Jiangxia district respiratory physician, the outbreak came, his department became the first line of fighting the epidemic. But on January 25, because of new coronavirus pneumonia, Peng Yinhua had to interrupt work, admitted to the ward, become a patient.

In fact, without the outbreak, Peng Yinhua's life would have only just begun. He was 29, approaching his 30th birthday, and only last year officially became a suction physician at the First People's Hospital in Jiangxia district; he and his wife were married for two years, he had planned a two-year-late wedding for her on February 1; his wife is six months pregnant and, not surprisingly, he will have a new identity as a "father" in June..

But at 21:50 on February 20, Peng Yinhua's life came to an abrupt end, after 27 consecutive days in the hospital, because the condition was getting worse, he died in Jinyintan hospital.

On February 21, the memorial service was held temporarily in the Lecture Hall on the Fifth Floor of the First People's Hospital in Jiangxia district. A simple portrait of Peng, in a bow tie and striped suit, is projected on a screen in front of the hall. It was a photograph he had prepared for the wedding, and now it was taken as a suicide photograph. Yellow and white daisies sit on the square table beneath the photo.

The last 20 days in the money pit

Peng spent his last 20 days in the hospital.

On January 30, his condition deteriorated and he was transferred to Golden Pond Hospital. Five days earlier, Peng Yinhua has undergone two nucleic acid tests, the final second test was confirmed as new coronary pneumonia.

Ling Yun, a nurse in the South Sixth Ward of the Intensive Care Unit of Jinyintan Hospital, appeared in her diary on the first day of her arrival at Jinyintan hospital with the Anhui medical team.

"The doctor's patient breathes rapidly up to 40-50 times per minute, and has deep and severe alkalosis, " Ling Yun wrote in his journal on the night of February 2, when he first saw Peng.

On the same day, after a series of treatment measures, Peng Yinhua's blood gas analysis finally approached the normal level and his appetite improved. He ate two semi-liquid foods and drank Baipuli (nutrient solution) . "Doctors and patients win the battle of the disease is in hand. ". Ling Yun wrote in his journal.

Peng Yinhua looked really good. On that day, out of recognition and gratitude for Ling Yun's nursing work, he also volunteered to add Ling Yun's wechat account. As soon as Ling Yun turned on his mobile phone after work that night, peng Yinhua's friend application jumped out: "The south first district, the 6th floor, the 6th bed, the patient you take care of" . He greeted Ling Yun, who had just left work, on Wechat and told him to rest and protect himself.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A chat between Peng Yinhua and a nurse named Ling Yun

Peng Yinhua, 6th floor and 6th bed, made a good impression on many nurses. In the non-invasive breathing machine and a variety of puncture, Peng Yinhua special cooperation. "We often have to pump the patient's artery to see how it's oxygenating, and it hurts when we pump, and sometimes it's hard to get an artery in, but he can just hold it in and let you do it, " Ling Yun said.

Because suck not smooth, most patient can feel special fatigue in weekday. Illness in the night brought more discomfort, Peng Yinhua in hospital during most of the habit of sleeping during the day, awake at night. Ling Yun advised him, "sleep less during the day, sleep at night, do not confuse the biological clock" , Ling Yun did not expect, Peng Yinhua soon listen to, a night to turn off the phone, quiet sleep.

The nurses watched the "doctor patient" as they looked through a glass window at the patient in the ward, where the machine showed "stable vital signs" and the patient's condition showed "stable mood" .

But the change came suddenly. On February 8, Peng Yinhua's heart rate accelerated. "At first it was in the 80s, then it reached around 130. " By 2:00 that afternoon, Peng Yinhua's blood oxygen saturation concentration also began to drop. Doctors gave him tracheal intubation treatment, boom-boom.

Followed by kidney and lung failure, "acid is particularly serious, the lungs of carbon dioxide can not come out" , "with suction machine two days later, found that there is no urine, began to do kidney dialysis. On Peng Yinhua's sudden change of condition, Ling Yun had asked the attending doctor, the doctor said Peng Yinhua is in an inflammatory storm, many seriously ill patients will experience, "if the patient survived, good, not over. ".

Peng Yinhua fell into a deep coma. On February 19, the hospital performed a plasma exchange for him. The nurse, Zhang Chunyan, stayed by Peng Yinhua's side for three hours and watched the 40 bags of 50 ml of plasma flow into Peng Yinhua's body with the Catheter, like a little bit of hope into the recovery, "we all hope that he will be better soon, " said Zhang Chunyan. When awake, Peng Yinhua once told nurses: The wife is pregnant, oneself is about to become a father.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Peng Yinhua's wedding photo

On the field of battle

Ling Yun heard from Peng about the new coronavirus infection. "In two days, he treated 300 patients, and his resistance was reduced because of fatigue. ".

At the time of the outbreak, it was only six months before Peng became a full-time doctor. In June 2015, Peng Yinhua was recruited for an internship at Jiangxia District's First People's Hospital. In 2016, after obtaining a medical license, he went to the headquarters of Union Medical College Hospital for a three-year training, he returned to the First People's Hospital in Jiangxia district in June 2019 and officially became a respiratory physician.

On January 21, Peng Yinhua's third ward of respiratory and critical care medicine was listed as the second batch of in-patient isolation ward for treating "viral pneumonia of unknown origin" .

Liu Bende, deputy director of the First People's Hospital in Jiangxia District, said in an interview with the media that the hospital had not been designated as a designated hospital at the beginning of the outbreak, if the city hospitals are closed, patients will flock here. As of February 14, the hospital admitted a total of nearly 600 new pneumonia patients.

His wife, Zhong Xin, recalled that since late January, Peng has been significantly busier. "He always worked overtime and often came home around 10 or 11 o'clock in the evening. ". After the establishment of the isolation ward of the hospital, Peng Yinhua, as a breathing physician, had to work "day shift and night shift" shifts. He became even busier, because he was afraid of bringing the risk of infection to his family, and Peng Yinhua was simply admitted to the hospital, and never came home again.

Peng Yinhua busy time in the hospital, Zhong Xin can only communicate with him through Wechat: "I told him not to be too tired, to pay attention to rest, he said not tired, said such busy let him feel very full. ".

The two only met once on the 30th day of the Lunar New Year. Zhong Xin went to the hospital to deliver daily necessities to Peng Yinhua. She put the things in the hospital's in-patient department and left. When Peng Yinhua came to pick them up, the husband and wife were standing face to face and talking on the phone at a distance of two to three hundred meters, at that time, Peng Yinhua wearing a mask and hat, can not see the expression, two people in the phone each other cheer, Zhong Xin far to give him than "V" , is a victory sign.

She didn't think it would be the last time she would see her husband.

"We don't want anything, just people. "

On January 25, Peng Yinhua became ill with "fever, cough and shortness of breath, " he told Zhong on Wechat. But Peng Yinhua colleague, Jiangxia District First People's hospital fever intensive care unit doctor Hu Jun Guess: "He may January 23,24 on a bit uncomfortable, but to 25 to attach importance, came to the hospital, was a little fever, dry cough, check the lung CT has a more typical lesion. ".

Peng was later hospitalized at Jiangxia District's First People's Hospital and was diagnosed on January 28 during a second nucleic acid test. "In fact, when he was treated at the First People's Hospital in Jiangxia, he was still in a good state. He spoke clearly and had a clear mind, " Zhong Xin said. After February 9, Peng Yinhua's condition deteriorated in Jinyintan hospital and he fell into a deep coma. Zhong Xin was extremely worried, calls the hospital every day for details.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Peng Yinhua at Jinyintan Hospital on Feb. 2

Peng Yinhua in Xiaogan Yunmeng county's parents, but also at this time just know son sick news. Before this, Peng Yinhua lets the wife conceal them. Peng Yinhua has a brother and sister, the third in the family, is the youngest one. "The first news we got was that the hospital told us on February 10 that he was in critical condition, and on February 11 that he was in critical condition, " Ms. Peng said in an interview. "The hospital asked us what we wanted. We don't want anything, as long as people are here! "

Relatives Rarely Associate Peng with the worst-case scenario: "He was so young and strong. ".

But the worst is yet to come. On February 20, Zhong received two phone calls from the hospital.

The first call was at 3:50 p.m. , and the caller said that they were in the emergency room. Zhong Xin was once a nurse at the First People's Hospital in Jiangxia district. "I already have a balance in my mind, " she said. But she was six months pregnant, so she tried to calm down, just as they had encouraged each other.

At 10:18 p.m. , the second call came, and when Zhong answered, she was shaking all over and could hardly contain herself.

The voice on the other end of the phone told her that Peng Yinhua had left.

"Big, dumb boy. "

The News of Peng's death came as a shock to many people late at night, most of whom knew him only when news of his death first came to light. In his eulogies, the words "down-to-earth" , "Sunshine" and "big boy" were mentioned several times.

In the six months we worked together at the First People's Hospital in Jiangxia District, "usually it's the nurses from the support center who come to accompany the check-up, but sometimes the support is too busy, " recalled Peng's colleague Hu Jun. "Dr. Peng comes out of his own volition. He can leave after the night shift at 8 o'clock, but he will accompany the patient for the check-up. It will take at least three hours. He will undertake some tasks that are not his own. "

While Peng was still in the Wuhan Union Hospital for a three-year training program, Doctor Zhang Jing (not his real name) was impressed by him. "He never makes a big deal out of anything. ". One Year Spring Festival, two people on duty in the hospital, two days in a dozen patients, too busy to worry, Zhang Jing looked at Peng Yinhua "run before and after, orderly, not in a hurry. ".

Zhang Jing saw Peng Yinhua last time, is last year in the hospital, he came to do the graduation procedures. Peng Yinhua chuckled and told himself, "teacher, I signed the Concord Jiangnan Hospital (that is, the First People's Hospital in Jiangxia district) . ".

After Peng's death, a widely circulated photograph taken by a nurse showed him lying on a bed in a hospital in Jinyintan with his hand outstretched. Zhang Jing looked sad, feel is familiar with Peng Yinhua, "sunshine, optimistic, like a 'big boy' . ".

"Big boy" Peng Yinhua Tall, honest, can work, in college was elected by roommate dormitory president, Wang Ruibo is Peng Yinhua in Hubei University of Science and technology when roommate, he felt that Peng Yinhua is not afraid of "loss. At that time, the responsibility of the dormitory director need to be responsible for a lot of "loss" of the work, dormitory on the fifth floor, drinking bottled water to buy from a long distance to move back to the dormitory, almost all are responsible for Peng Yinhua.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Peng Yinhua and his college roommate, second from the left, Peng Yinhua. Source

Also often have "lose" live find Peng Yinhua, four in the morning, class female students abdominal pain to see a doctor, class teacher a phone call to him, he also said nothing, the students back down to the fifth floor and then to the school gate.

Peng's family was poor and his parents were small traders in their hometown in Xiaogan, Yunmeng County, Wang said. In 2014, Peng's father was diagnosed with a brain aneurysm and cerebral infarction. During the program, roommate often complained about the low salary of 3,000 to 4,000 yuan, but he was surprised that Peng could squeeze out some money for his parents under such circumstances.

His wife Zhong Xin also mentioned that even after Peng took a formal job, his first salary went to his parents. When they first met, Peng Yinhua was a doctor at the First People's Hospital in Jiangxia district and Zhong Xin was a nurse. The couple married in 2017, but the ceremony was never held because of work and financial reasons.

The belated wedding was originally planned for Feb. 1, the eighth day of the Lunar New Year, at Peng Yinhua's hometown of Xiaogan Yunmeng. On December 8th Ms Peng told roommate at Qunli. Later, because of the epidemic, the invitation cards that couldn't be sent out were stuffed into a drawer in the office.

When the bad news came, in Peng Yinhua's group of college roommates, known as "best friends, " former roommates changed their wechat profiles into a candle flame. They stayed up all night, and as a sign of mourning, they opened the group chat voice, from the first meeting with Peng Yinhua to now.

Peng Yinhua likes children, he began to look forward to Zhong Xin's early pregnancy. Now the father, Peng Yinhua, will be a role model in the stories Chung will tell her children.
